Can we do questions at the end?

00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:08.000
Yeah, that's fine.

00:13:08.000 --> 00:13:10.000
Perfect. All right.

00:13:11.000 --> 00:13:13.000
So we have data.

00:13:13.000 --> 00:13:15.000
We will now tidy it.

00:13:15.000 --> 00:13:18.000
This is a hard, very overwhelming question.

00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:22.000
And it kind of starts with, what does my data even look like to start?

00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:24.000
You know, what are the columns?

00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:26.000
What are some summary statistics?

00:13:26.000 --> 00:13:30.000
Can I quickly open all of these files of data that I have on my computer?

00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:31.000
And the answer is yes.

00:13:31.000 --> 00:13:33.000
So this is built into Positron.

00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:36.000
This is our data explorer.

00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:39.000
If you click on a Pollers or Pandas data frame,

00:13:39.000 --> 00:13:44.000
or if you open it up from the Variables pane, which you'll see shortly,

00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:47.000
you get this beautifully full-featured data explorer.

00:13:47.000 --> 00:13:52.000
It has things like summary statistics.

00:13:52.000 --> 00:13:56.000
It has little sparklines for your data.

00:13:56.000 --> 00:14:00.000
You can sort of like debug your data by quickly scrolling through it.

00:14:00.000 --> 00:14:03.000
And this is a data explorer that's highly performant.

00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:07.000
We've had tests with tens of millions of rows and millions of columns.

00:14:07.000 --> 00:14:12.000
And it acts pretty much the same as if you had like 30 rows.

00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:14.000
It's kind of magic how it works.

00:14:14.000 --> 00:14:20.000
And I'm always impressed by how large of data sets people are using in this data explorer.

00:14:20.000 --> 00:14:24.000
And something that's new, and I think just the most beautiful thing I've ever seen,

00:14:24.000 --> 00:14:28.000
is you can also click on CSV or Parquet files,

00:14:28.000 --> 00:14:31.000
and they automatically open in your data explorer.

00:14:31.000 --> 00:14:34.000
You don't need to be running Python, you don't need to be running R,

00:14:34.000 --> 00:14:36.000
you don't need to be running Julia,

00:14:36.000 --> 00:14:40.000
because this is using DuckDB with WebAssembly code to automatically load it,

00:14:40.000 --> 00:14:42.000
so it's very fast.

00:14:42.000 --> 00:14:45.000
And, I mean, how many times have people tried to open a Parquet file,

00:14:45.000 --> 00:14:47.000
and then you have to think about like, ah, time to go to Python,

00:14:47.000 --> 00:14:50.000
time to click all these boilerplate buttons.

00:14:50.000 --> 00:14:53.000
Like, it seems simple, but I feel like this is so magical

00:14:53.000 --> 00:14:56.000
to be able to just see your data so easily.

00:14:56.000 --> 00:14:58.000
So this is new.

00:14:58.000 --> 00:15:02.000
Our data explorer is something we're super proud of

00:15:02.000 --> 00:15:05.000
and is continuing to transform.

